The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec. 15: The Supreme Court today asked the Centre to explain why it had raised the yearly income limit for OBC reservation benefits when the ceiling was aimed at keeping the creamy layer out.          otices came on a petition filed by the Nair Service Society, which challenged the October 13 decision to raise the limit from Rs 2.5 lakh a year to Rs 4.5 lakh.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has granted N.D. Tiwari exemption from personal appearance in a paternity case. The Andhra Pradesh governor is locked in a legal battle with 29-year-old Rohit Shekhar, who claims to be his son.                  
	 Mumbai: Hasan Ali Khan, the Pune-based race horse owner accused of money laundering, has been arrested for allegedly securing several fake passports. Khan was held when he arrived in Mumbai to complete some paperwork in the passport case in Bombay High Court. He had been declared a proclaimed offender by a magistrates court in April this year.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): The Maharashtra government has issued notices to producers of TV shows featuring children, seeking a description of the work environment provided to them. There have been reports that these children are made to work 12 to 14 hours at a stretch.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A casual Metro worker was arrested on Monday for making a hoax call on December 6, saying a bomb had been planted at the Rajiv Chowk Metro station. Prashant Pandey, 22, had made the call from the station.                                                                                                                         
